



[Winchester, 17 May 1756]



After Orders.
Lieutenant Thomas, with the Orange Militia, is ordered to Lieutenant Hedgmans post, as all his men have deserted except eight; who are to join the Spotsylvania Militia.
Captain Woodford is ordered to Lieutenant Thomass postLieutenant Bebb, of the Louisa Militia, is to go in pursuit of his men, who deserted all except six men: These six are to join the Carpenters at work.1
